1). To link the css file

<link rel="spreadsheet" href="filename">


2). To link the js file

<script src="filename"></script>

3). To add the links in the site (Anchor tag)

    <a href="link address">Name</a>
    (It will open the link in the same page)

    (To open the page in the anothetr tab , we have to add <_blank>)

    <a target="_blank" href="link address">Name</a>


4). To add image in the site

    <img src="saved file name(included in the file manager)" alt="Image name(According to us)">

    (we can also add height and width to it)

    <img width="in px" height="in px" src="saved file name(included in the file manager)"
        alt="Image name(According to us)">

5). Break tag


    to leave the space after the image and start with a new line
    <br>


6). To make a table using table tag and using caption tag

    <table>

        <caption>Tble name</caption>

        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Anything</th>
            <th>Everything</th>
        </tr>


        <tr>
            <td>Any</td>
            <td>Any</td>
            <td>Any</td>
        </tr>

    </table>

    (tr ---> table row)
    (th ---> table heading)
    (td ---> table data)

    It has two attributes [1). Colspan , 2). Rowspan]

    <td colspan="2">Any</td>
    (Any will take 2 places in the column of the table)

    <td rowspan="2">Any</td>
    (Any will take 2 places in the row of the table)



7). Lists

    1). unordered Lists
    (we can add the shapes to the list bullets)
    <ul type="square,circle,etc">
        <li>asm</li>
        <li>msa</li>
        <li>sam</li>
    </ul>

    2). Ordered Lists

    <ol type="I,i,1 (by default), a, A">
        <li>asm</li>
        <li>msa</li>
        <li>sam</li>
    </ol>

    indexing
    I --> upper case roman numbers
    i --> lower case roman numbers
    a --> lower case alphabets
    A --> upper case alphabets


    3). Detailed list



8). meta:desc
    (is used to give the brief description about the web site generally which appears below the site name in the google)


9). Forms

    <form action=""></form>


    <form action="/submit-url" method="post">
  <label for="username">Username:</label>
  <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>

  <label for="password">Password:</label>
  <input type="password" id="password" name="password">

  <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>


// css

can be added in html using style tag
